<subSubSection id="02088C415FE96F75B5640C2B0BBBC1E7" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" type="original description">
<paragraph id="93C8B513B344A491BD92A8112D32DE01" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Original description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34C6F2C6B2BB218DF112C2C04E30EA2E" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">A. punctigerum: niger, elytris nigris, striatis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9390D0B5AECC6F77001F877AFA305C26" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Habitat in Smolandia Sveciae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51504BBC1736A305733612E6F903EC1D" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Magnitudine pediculi totus opacus, niger.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="30A428CBA4809965A59F9CE405AC4F7D" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Elytra gibba, striata, atra.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D919514A2D6B441BB72B0EBD3BB75131" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" type="material studied">
<paragraph id="C46C52520D69F0FCAA26C2A8BFFDD484" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">Material studied.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A6F5BBA40F7BB33227E69A169E08F95" pageId="4" pageNumber="93">
I have received three specimens, as follows: one divided into three parts and glued onto a square white card, this on a short thin pin with head, with data: 543a, Mus. Thunb.; one headless, worn, pinned high on a long thin pin with head, with data: 543b, Mus. Thunb.; and a third glued to a rectangular label, this on a short thick pin with head, with data: 1191, Smol. The first specimen is a female of 
<taxonomicName id="00AF5BF69CF592637B1E549071FD8A62" authority="Schilsky, 1901" authorityName="Schilsky" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Aspidapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidapion radiolus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radiolus">Aspidapion radiolus</taxonomicName>
(Marsham, 1802), the second a female of either 
<taxonomicName id="62C515D0C5EE84D4267C9DCC6B4BAF5E" authority="Schilsky, 1901" authorityName="Schilsky" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Ceratapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ceratapion gibbirostre" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbirostre">Ceratapion gibbirostre</taxonomicName>
(Gyllenhal, 1813) or 
<taxonomicName id="F85E4CEDCC5A39BD8F59EFEA0BB6FAA5" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Curculio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Curculio carduorum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carduorum">Curculio carduorum</taxonomicName>
(Kirby, 1808), and the third is an etiolated (probably female) specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="2DFB662992C8C89CEEBBE6E8892814BE" authority="Bokor, 1923" authorityName="Bokor" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Ischnopterapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ischnopterapion (Ischnopterapion) loti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loti" subGenus="Ischnopterapion">Ischnopterapion (Ischnopterapion) loti</taxonomicName>
(Kirby, 1808). The first two are coloured brightly, with the elytra more or less metallic, and do not fit 
<normalizedToken id="75FB8E546C8FACAD5AEA67139FEE619B" originalValue="Thunberg’s">Thunberg's</normalizedToken>
description. The third fits 
<normalizedToken id="C0122BCF4EDA0E4DFACAAA36EEB76B21" originalValue="Thunberg’s">Thunberg's</normalizedToken>
description, although the body colour has become brownish, and is labelled with the type locality, Smolandia (= 
<normalizedToken id="EF6E65AEAB8991EF13FCCB1CF1F75A8F" originalValue="Småland">Smaland</normalizedToken>
, Sweden). I hereby designate this specimen as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="555C18CC63085AA5CC1548A5900C65F6" authority="Herbst, 1797" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1797" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Apion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apion punctigerum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctigerum">Apion punctigerum</taxonomicName>
Thunberg, 1815, and its name becomes a new synonym of that of 
<taxonomicName id="02AA0D8D574543421CA591B11839EF46" authority="Bokor, 1923" authorityName="Bokor" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Apionidae" genus="Ischnopterapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ischnopterapion loti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loti">Ischnopterapion loti</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
